---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Styling">
  <h1>Styling</h1>
  <p class="lead">SliderKit adds BEM class names to every element it creates. Override them with plain CSS — no preprocessor needed.</p>

  <h2>DOM structure</h2>
  <p>After init, the slider wraps your container in this structure:</p>
  <pre><code>div.c--slider-a__outer          ← position:relative, arrows mount here
  div.c--slider-a__overflow     ← overflow:hidden, clips the track
    div.c--slider-a__inner      ← applies edgePadding margin
      div#your-id               ← your original container (the track)
        div.c--slider-a__item   ← each slide
      /div
    /div
  /div
  div.c--slider-a__pagination   ← pagination mounts here
/div</code></pre>

  <h2>State classes</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Class</th><th>Applied to</th><th>When</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>.c--slider-a--horizontal</code></td><td>container</td><td>Always (horizontal axis).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>.c--slider-a--vertical</code></td><td>container</td><td>When <code>axis:'vertical'</code>.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>.c--slider-a__item--active</code></td><td>slide</td><td>Slide is in the visible range.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>.c--slider-a__item--clone</code></td><td>slide</td><td>Clone slide (loop only).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>.c--slider-a--frozen</code></td><td>outer wrapper</td><td>Slider is frozen (all slides fit, <code>freezable:true</code>).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>.c--slider-a--autoplay-playing</code></td><td>outer wrapper</td><td>Autoplay is running.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>.c--slider-a--autoplay-paused</code></td><td>outer wrapper</td><td>Autoplay is paused.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Customising arrows</h2>
  <pre><code>/* size and position */
.c--slider-a__arrow {"{"}
  width: 48px;
  height: 48px;
  border-radius: 4px;          /* square instead of circle */
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
{"}"}

/* placement */
.c--slider-a__arrow--prev {"{"} left: 0; {"}"}
.c--slider-a__arrow--next {"{"} right: 0; {"}"}

/* disabled state */
.c--slider-a__arrow--disabled {"{"}
  opacity: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
{"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>Customising dots</h2>
  <pre><code>/* dot shape */
.c--slider-a__pagination-bullet {"{"}
  width: 8px;
  height: 8px;
  border-radius: 2px;          /* square dots */
  background: #d1d5db;
{"}"}

/* active dot */
.c--slider-a__pagination-bullet--active {"{"}
  background: #6C2BD9;
  transform: scale(1.4);
{"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>Highlighting the active slide</h2>
  <pre><code>/* dim all slides, brighten the active one */
.c--slider-a__item {"{"}
  opacity: 0.4;
  transition: opacity 0.3s;
{"}"}
.c--slider-a__item--active {"{"}
  opacity: 1;
{"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>Vertical arrows</h2>
  <p>For <code>axis:'vertical'</code> the default arrow positions (left/right) don't make sense. Override them to top/bottom:</p>
  <pre><code>.c--slider-a__arrow {"{"}
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
{"}"}
.c--slider-a__arrow--prev {"{"} top: 8px; {"}"}
.c--slider-a__arrow--next {"{"} bottom: 8px; top: auto; {"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>Hide controls when frozen</h2>
  <p>When <code>freezable:true</code> and all slides fit, the outer wrapper gets <code>.c--slider-a--frozen</code>. You can use this to hide controls:</p>
  <pre><code>.c--slider-a--frozen .c--slider-a__arrow,
.c--slider-a--frozen .c--slider-a__pagination {"{"}
  display: none;
{"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>Autoplay state styling</h2>
  <pre><code>/* show a pause icon when playing, play icon when paused */
.c--slider-a--autoplay-playing .my-play-btn  {"{"} display: none; {"}"}
.c--slider-a--autoplay-paused  .my-pause-btn {"{"} display: none; {"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>Dark mode</h2>
  <pre><code>@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {"{"}
  .c--slider-a__arrow {"{"}
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    color: #fff;
  {"}"}
  .c--slider-a__pagination-bullet {"{"}
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
  {"}"}
  .c--slider-a__pagination-bullet--active {"{"}
    background: #a78bfa;
  {"}"}
{"}"}</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
